Tombini’s Remark About Brazil Rates Misinterpreted, Person Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-04-16T17:19:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/tombini-s-remark-about-brazil-rates-misinterpreted-person-says.html
Brazilian central bank president
Alexandre Tombini’s remark yesterday that the country is “in
the middle of a tightening cycle” did not intend to convey any
message about the length or scale of the cycle, said a person
familiar with the central bank’s decision-making process, who
requested anonymity citing internal policy.  Investors over-interpreted the remark, which Tombini used
to mean in the process of, rather than halfway through, the
person said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Washington at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  